# Ask before modifying stock shadcn components

The vendored shadcn/ui primitives in `src/renderer/components/ui/**` are
**CLI-generated from our preset** (see [`docs/shadcn.md`](../../docs/shadcn.md)).
A re-theme (`shadcn apply`) reinstalls them, so any hand-edit silently drifts from —
or gets clobbered by — the source of truth. Treat them as generated, not hand-authored.

## The rule

**Before editing ANY file under `src/renderer/components/ui/**`, STOP and ask me
first.** In the same message, tell me:

1. Which primitive(s) you want to change and the exact diff.
2. Why the change is necessary.
3. What non-invasive alternatives you considered (see below).

Do not make the edit until I explicitly approve it.

## Prefer these over editing the primitive

- **Pass `className`** at the call site — the primitives merge it via `cn(...)`,
 so most tweaks (spacing, sizing, positioning) need zero edits to `ui/**`.
- **Wrap** the primitive in an app-level component under `components/` (not `ui/`).
- **Re-theme** through the documented preset flow if the change is design-wide.

## If I approve an edit

Record it in the "Local modifications to re-apply on reinstall" list in
[`docs/shadcn.md`](../../docs/shadcn.md), with the reason, so a future re-theme
re-applies it. An undocumented deviation is a bug.
